- Use `@EnableCaching` annotation in your configuration class to enable caching.
- Configure `RedisCacheManager` bean for Redis caching:
  ```java
  @Bean
  public RedisCacheManager cacheManager(RedisConnectionFactory connectionFactory) {
      return RedisCacheManager.builder(connectionFactory)
          .cacheDefaults(CacheConfiguration.defaultCacheConfig().entryTtl(Duration.ofMinutes(10)))
          .build();
  }
  ```
- Use `@Cacheable`, `@CachePut`, and `@CacheEvict` annotations on your repository methods.
- Ensure Redis is running and accessible from your application.
- Update Spring Data JPA to version 2.7.x or later for the latest features and improvements.
- Update Spring Data Redis to version 2.7.x or later for the latest features and improvements.
- Key config options include `entryTtl` (time-to-live) for cache entries, `cacheDefaults` for default cache settings, and `RedisConnectionFactory` for connecting to Redis.
